Kiola Nut <br>
Koalindl Fish <br>
Honey Jum<br>
Erud's Tonic <br>
<br>
Resulting item:<br>
Stein of Mogguk<br>
Magic/lore item<br>
Dex +5 Int +10 HP +10 sv Disease + 25<br>
1 charge of Light Healing<br>
Wt. 2.5<br>
All/all <br>
Cannot be recharged<br>
<br>
All four ingredients must be given to Gregor in the Inn on the docks in East Freeport. Be careful as there are two paladins in Gregor’s Inn during the day that will kill a Dark Elf. At night, they are replaced by a dark elf and a gnome, which appear to be non-kos to dark elves. Gregor will give you the Bartenders Compendium. This is a lore/no drop item. Take the compendium to Clurg in Ogguk. Clurg will then give you the stein. <br>
<br>
Kiloa Nuts can sometimes be found at vendors other than the one on Sister Isle, but don’t count on it. If you plan on doing this quest more than once, buy more than one kiloa nut.<br>
<br>
The Koalindl Fish must be killed to obtain the needed item. Be ware, if you get to close to the guard, he will kill you. The fish is a lore/no drop item and does not drop every time. I suggest camping your enchanter in the pond and making a human or half elf mule to kill the fish. A bard works pretty well, but you may want to lvl him up until he gets a damage song before killing the fish. Killing the fish will get you bad faction with the Temple.<br>
<br>
Honey Jum is a quest in itself. You need to gather three honey combs from the bixies in Kith, or Misty Thicket if you can get in. Killing bixies will increase your faction with Rivervale. Take the honey combs and 30 gp (cannot be platinum) to the merchant in The Herb Jar. You don’t have to talk to her, just give her the items, unstacked, and the cash and she will give you the honey jum.<br>
<br>
Erud’s Tonic – Another quest in itself, you will need to venture to Erudin for this. Go to the Blue Hawk’s Inn and buy an Innoruuk’s Kiss of Death (lore item). Take the drink to Sinnkin Highbrow on the top floor of the Library. She will give you Erud’s Tonic (lore/no drop).<br>
<br>
Repeatedly doing this quest will raise some Oggok factions so that you don’t need to cast illusion/benevolence  to turn the times in.<br>
